([ "Account":"ezralee", "Assigned":"", "AssistText":"! PAINTING ! painting of a castle in the Scottish highlands. With dark, moody skies and an arresting view of the Scottish highlands, this painting features an ancient stone castle in the background, stark in contrast to the vivid viridian hues of the grass that extend along the rolling hills beyond. The most predominant focus of the painting is not the landscape but the trio of individuals standing in the image's foreground. A mother and son, both auburn-haired and nearly matching in height, stand hand-in-hand facing the viewer, their riotous curls blowing in the wind that sweeps their curls into frozen motion, their serene smiles crinkling their hazel eyes beneath the matching iron diadems over their brows. Behind them, towering in height, stands a man with unruly blond hair that matches the long beard upon his face, his blue eyes crinkled with a toothy smile. His hands rest upon the shoulders of the figures before him, holding them close and watching over them. Tucked in the grasses at the bottom corner of the canvas, the signature Dalena is nearly invisible in a dark crimson script.
